HEADWORD: Strangles
<hw>Stran"gles</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A disease in horses
and swine, in which the upper part of the throat, or groups of lymphatic
glands elsewhere, swells.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Strangulate</ent>⟦br⟧
